# Keep the build context lean AND ensure gitignored/secret/large assets can never enter
# the image (CLAUDE.md §12/§12a/§14). The runtime image gets ONLY compiled gateway code.
# NOTE: .dockerignore does not support trailing inline comments — each pattern is its own
# line, comments are whole lines only.

# VCS + CI metadata
.git
.github

# Gradle / Kotlin build state (rebuilt inside the image)
.gradle
.kotlin
**/build

# RuneLite client tree — must never be shipped or launched (CLAUDE.md §12a)
client

# 500M+ cache dump — bind-mounted read-only at runtime instead of baked in
cache-data
cache-out
content/items
content/npcs
content/objects

# Gateway RSA private key — secret, bind-mounted at runtime, never in an image layer (§14)
server-rsa.properties

# Deploy / CI / meta files — not needed to compile, and kept out so editing them does not
# bust the (expensive) source COPY + compile layer.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
compose.yml
scripts
.gitignore
gradlew.bat
CLAUDE.md

# Editor / docs / local tooling not needed to build
.idea
docs
.actrc
.git-pat
